---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../../components/Navbar.astro';

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [
    { params: { slug: 'bmi-chart-for-men-women' }, props: { title: 'BMI Chart for Men and Women', category: 'GUIDE' } },
    { params: { slug: 'healthy-bmi-range-indians' }, props: { title: 'Healthy BMI Range for Indians', category: 'RESEARCH' } },
    { params: { slug: 'bmi-calculator-teens' }, props: { title: 'BMI Calculator for Teens', category: 'ADOLESCENCE' } }
  ];
}

const { title, category } = Astro.props;
---

<Layout 
    title={`${title} | Real BMI`}
    description={`Learn more about ${title} with Real BMI's deep health insights.`}
>
    <Navbar />
    <main class="pt-40 pb-20 px-6 min-h-screen">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto glass-card p-8 md:p-16 space-y-12 border-2 border-[var(--border)]">
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <a href="/en" class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--accent)] flex items-center gap-2 hover:translate-x-[-4px] transition-transform">
                    <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18" /></svg>
                    Return Home
                </a>
                <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black tracking-tighter uppercase text-[var(--foreground)] leading-tight">{title}</h1>
                <p class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-[var(--accent)]">{category}</p>
            </div>

            <div class="prose prose-zinc dark:prose-invert max-w-none text-[var(--muted-foreground)] leading-relaxed space-y-8 text-lg font-bold opacity-70">
                <p>
                    Body Mass Index (BMI) is a standardized measure used worldwide to compare weight relative to height. It is one of the fastest ways to understand whether a person is underweight, healthy, overweight, or obese, but it is best used as part of a broader health assessment.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-[var(--foreground)] uppercase tracking-tight">Why BMI Matters for Men and Women</h2>
                <p>
                    Men and women carry weight differently, and BMI is a useful starting point for identifying major health patterns. While it does not directly measure body fat, it helps highlight when a bodyweight falls outside of the clinically recommended range.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-[var(--foreground)] uppercase tracking-tight">How to Use the BMI Chart</h2>
                <p>
                    The BMI chart is designed to make insights immediate and actionable. Use it together with the Real BMI Calculator to compare your result against trusted global thresholds from the World Health Organization (WHO) and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-[var(--foreground)] uppercase tracking-tight">Keep It Practical</h2>
                <p>
                    Your BMI result is a useful health signal, not a diagnosis. For people with higher muscle mass, athletes, or those with unique body composition, BMI should be combined with other metrics such as body fat percentage, waist-to-hip ratio, and metabolic health.
                </p>

                <p>
                    This classification follows official global guidelines from the <b><u>World Health Organization (WHO)</u></b> and the <b><u>CDC</u></b>, ensuring you are viewing the metric through a modern, evidence-based lens.
                </p>

                <div class="pt-8 border-t border-[var(--border)]">
                    <a href="/en#calculator" class="calc-btn-gradient px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-black uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest inline-block transition-all hover:scale-105 active:scale-95">
                        Back to Calculator
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
